2. Linear Regression with variables selected using AIC

library(leaps)
n = length(train$siri)
b = regsubsets(siri ~ ., data = train, nvmax = 15)
rs = summary(b)
aic = n*log(rs$rss/n) + 2*(2:16)
i = which.min(aic)
plot(aic ~ I(1:15), ylab = "AIC", xlab = "Number of Predictors", type = "o", col = c("black", "red")[as.factor(c(1:(i-1)*0,1,(1:15 - i))*0)])

trainAIC = train[, rs$which[i,]]
lmodAIC = lm(siri ~ ., data = trainAIC);
summary(lmodAIC)

The morley data can be viewed as a randomized block experiment with Run as the treatment factor and Expt as the blocking factor.

Is there a difference between runs and what efficiency is gained by blocking? (Make sure factors are stored in R as factors!)

library(faraway)
data(morley)

head(morley)
##     Expt Run Speed
## 001    1   1   850
## 002    1   2   740
## 003    1   3   900
## 004    1   4  1070

## 006    1   6   850
lmod = lm(Speed ~ Expt*Run, data = morley)
anova = aov(lmod)
summary(anova)

## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
